The paper deals with the design of logic circuits based on graph theory concepts, specifically zero forcing. This suggests that the paper may belong to the Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) category. The paper also discusses the evaluation of Boolean functions, which is a topic in Computational Complexity (cs.CC) and Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). The mention of "reversible computation" suggests a possible connection to Emerging Technologies (cs.ET) and Quantum Physics (cs.QL).
